Package: catalystanalyticsr
Type: Package
Title: Sustainable Development Scenario Engine for the Catalyst Suite
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(person("Tariq", "Ahmad", email = "tariq@thecontentcatalyst.net", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Catalyst Analytics R is a sustainable-development analytics engine that simulates vector
    dynamical systems (calculus), computes inclusive-wealth indicators (e.g., Adjusted Net Savings),
    evaluates climate and carbon budgets, greenhouse-gas inventories, Kaya decompositions, capital stock-and-flow accounts, inclusive wealth, Adjusted Net Savings, human development, distribution, intergenerational equity, transparent composite scores, natural-capital accounts, sustainability boundaries, governed model calibration, historical and holdout validation, residual diagnostics, numerical solver benchmarks, stability testing, model cards, lifecycle governance, reproducible analytical projects, run histories, environment capture, portable publication bundles, Quarto and HTML outputs, governed Decision Studio and Knowledge Library handoffs, stable public API governance, release-readiness assessment, compatibility manifests, and production release controls; imports and validates documented datasets; computes governed indicators; propagates declared uncertainty; runs sensitivity and stress tests; and produces reproducible tables,
    plots, and export bundles for the broader Catalyst product suite.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    jsonlite,
    grid,
    rlang
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
